==English==

===Etymology===
{{etyl|enm|en}}, from {{etyl|fro}} {{term|pavemant|lang=fro}}<!--Chrétien de Troyes, circa 1176-->, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|pavimentum||lang=la|a hard surface, a pounded surface}}, from {{term|pavio|pavere|lang=la|to beat, to ram, to tread down}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-|s}}

# {{chiefly|British}} A [[pave]]d footpath at the side of a [[road]].
# {{US}} {{uncountable}} Paved [[exterior]] surface, as with a road or [[sidewalk]].
# The interior [[flooring]], especially when of stone, of large buildings such as a [[cathedral]].

